<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Comments: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Many commenters from university rehabilitation training programs expressed concern that programs at their institutions
might be discontinued if Federal funds were required to be directed to student support rather than for paying for instructional
costs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Discussion: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Existing regulations require academic training projects with a multi-year project period to increase the grantee's
share of teaching costs progressively in each succeeding year so that total personnel costs are fully absorbed by
the grantee at the termination of the project period. The 75 percent requirement provides greater latitude than existing
regulations.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

